{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01SiJUYh4Hpr3i1epDBcXJqe","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t---\n2\tstepsCompleted: [1, 2, 3, 4]\n3\tinputDocuments:\n4\t  - architecture-v3.md\n5\t  - tech-spec-retro-pipeline-harness-fixes.md\n6\t  - tech-spec-rust-stack-support.md\n7\t  - tech-spec-multi-stack-support.md\n8\t---\n9\t\n10\t# Architecture v3 — Epic Breakdown\n11\t\n12\t## Overview\n13\t\n14\t6 migration phases from architecture-v3.md, mapped to epics 10-15. Each epic ships working software. No backward compatibility — breaking changes are acceptable. State migration handles upgrades automatically.\n15\t\n16\t## Epic List\n17\t\n18\t- **Epic 10: Stack Provider Pattern** — Eliminate 41 if/else branches. One file per language.\n19\t- **Epic 11: Unified State** — Consolidate 5 state files into 2. Schema versioning.\n20\t- **Epic 12: lib/ Restructuring** — Split oversized files. Domain subdirectories. Thin commands.\n21\t- **Epic 13: Agent Abstraction** — Ralph behind an interface. 28 files decoupled.\n22\t- **Epic 14: Process & Infra Fixes** — Retro pipeline, tech debt gate, Docker pre-check, observability choice, verify provisioning.\n23\t- **Epic 15: Enforcement** — CI file size gate, ESLint rules, boundary tests, template migration.\n24\t\n25\t---\n26\t\n27\t## Epic 10: Stack Provider Pattern\n28\t\n29\tEliminate all stack conditionals outside `src/lib/stacks/`. Adding a language = adding one file.\n30\t\n31\t### Story 10-1: Create StackProvider interface and registry\n32\t\n33\tAs a developer,\n34\tI want a StackProvider interface that encapsulates all language-specific behavior,\n35\tSo that adding a new language requires only one new file.\n36\t\n37\t**Acceptance Criteria:**\n38\t\n39\t**Given** `src/lib/stacks/types.ts` exists\n40\t**When** inspected\n41\t**Then** it defines `StackProvider` interface with: `name`, `markers`, `displayName`, `detectAppType()`, `getCoverageTool()`, `detectCoverageConfig()`, `getOtlpPackages()`, `installOtlp()`, `getDockerfileTemplate()`, `getDockerBuildStage()`, `getRuntimeCopyDirectives()`, `getBuildCommands()`, `getTestCommands()`, `getSemgrepLanguages()`, `parseTestOutput()`, `parseCoverageReport()`, `getProjectName()`\n42\t\n43\t**Given** `src/lib/stacks/registry.ts` exists\n44\t**When** `detectStacks()` is called\n45\t**Then** it uses the registry's marker list (not hardcoded checks) to detect stacks\n46\t\n47\t**Given** the registry\n48\t**When** `getStackProvider('nodejs')` is called\n49\t**Then** it returns the NodejsProvider instance\n50\t\n51\t### Story 10-2: Implement NodejsProvider\n52\t\n53\tAs a developer,\n54\tI want all Node.js-specific logic in one file,\n55\tSo that Node.js behavior is encapsulated and testable in isolation.\n56\t\n57\t**Acceptance Criteria:**\n58\t\n59\t**Given** `src/lib/stacks/nodejs.ts` exists\n60\t**When** inspected\n61\t**Then** it implements all `StackProvider` methods for Node.js: package.json detection, vitest/jest/c8 coverage, npm OTLP packages, Dockerfile template, AGENTS.md commands\n62\t\n63\t**Given** the NodejsProvider\n64\t**When** `detectCoverageConfig()` is called on a project with vitest\n65\t**Then** it returns the same result as the current `detectNodeCoverageTool()`\n66\t\n67\t**Given** all Node.js if/else branches are removed from `coverage.ts`, `otlp.ts`, `docs-scaffold.ts`, `dockerfile-template.ts`\n68\t**When** `npm test` runs\n69\t**Then** all tests pass (0 regressions)\n70\t\n71\t### Story 10-3: Implement PythonProvider\n72\t\n73\tAs a developer,\n74\tI want all Python-specific logic in one file,\n75\tSo that Python behavior is encapsulated and testable in isolation.\n76\t\n77\t**Acceptance Criteria:**\n78\t\n79\t**Given** `src/lib/stacks/python.ts` exists\n80\t**When** inspected\n81\t**Then** it implements all `StackProvider` methods for Python: requirements.txt/pyproject.toml/setup.py detection, coverage.py, pip/pipx OTLP packages, Dockerfile template\n82\t\n83\t**Given** all Python if/else branches are removed from consumer files\n84\t**When** `npm test` runs\n85\t**Then** all tests pass\n86\t\n87\t### Story 10-4: Implement RustProvider\n88\t\n89\tAs a developer,\n90\tI want all Rust-specific logic in one file,\n91\tSo that Rust behavior is encapsulated and testable in isolation.\n92\t\n93\t**Acceptance Criteria:**\n94\t\n95\t**Given** `src/lib/stacks/rust.ts` exists\n96\t**When** inspected\n97\t**Then** it implements all `StackProvider` methods for Rust: Cargo.toml detection, app type (CLI/server/library/agent), cargo-tarpaulin, cargo add OTLP, multi-stage Dockerfile, `[dependencies.foo]` subsection parsing, `'library'` AppType\n98\t\n99\t**Given** all Rust if/else branches are removed from consumer files\n100\t**When** `npm test` runs\n101\t**Then** all tests pass\n102\t\n103\t### Story 10-5: Migrate all consumers to use StackProvider\n104\t\n105\tAs a developer,\n106\tI want zero `if (stack === 'nodejs')` patterns outside `src/lib/stacks/`,\n107\tSo that the stack abstraction doesn't leak.\n108\t\n109\t**Acceptance Criteria:**\n110\t\n111\t**Given** `coverage.ts`, `otlp.ts`, `docs-scaffold.ts`, `dockerfile-template.ts`, `verify/env.ts`, `readme.ts`\n112\t**When** inspected\n113\t**Then** zero stack string comparisons remain — all use `provider.method()`\n114\t\n115\t**Given** a boundary test exists\n116\t**When** it scans `src/` for `stack === 'nodejs'` or `stack === 'python'` or `stack === 'rust'` outside `src/lib/stacks/`\n117\t**Then** it finds zero matches\n118\t\n119\t---\n120\t\n121\t## Epic 11: Unified State\n122\t\n123\tConsolidate 5 state files into 2. Schema versioning. Derived views.\n124\t\n125\t### Story 11-1: Unified SprintState schema with versioning\n126\t\n127\tAs a developer,\n128\tI want one `sprint-state.json` with a versioned schema that contains all sprint runtime data,\n129\tSo that state is never out of sync.\n130\t\n131\t**Acceptance Criteria:**\n132\t\n133\t**Given** `sprint-state.json` has `version: 2` schema\n134\t**When** inspected\n135\t**Then** it contains: `stories`, `retries`, `flagged`, `epics`, `session`, `observability`, `run`\n136\t\n137\t**Given** an old `sprint-state.json` without `version` field\n138\t**When** `readSprintState()` is called\n139\t**Then** it auto-migrates to version 2 schema\n140\t\n141\t**Given** `.story_retries` and `.flagged_stories` files exist\n142\t**When** migration runs\n143\t**Then** their data is merged into `sprint-state.json` and the files are deleted\n144\t\n145\t### Story 11-2: sprint-status.yaml becomes derived view\n146\t\n147\tAs a developer,\n148\tI want `sprint-status.yaml` generated from `sprint-state.json`,\n149\tSo that there's one source of truth with a human-readable view.\n150\t\n151\t**Acceptance Criteria:**\n152\t\n153\t**Given** `sprint-state.json` has story statuses\n154\t**When** `generateSprintStatusYaml()` is called\n155\t**Then** it writes a valid YAML file matching the current sprint-status.yaml format\n156\t\n157\t**Given** a story status changes in `sprint-state.json`\n158\t**When** `writeSprintState()` completes\n159\t**Then** `sprint-status.yaml` is regenerated automatically\n160\t\n161\t**Given** harness-run reads story statuses\n162\t**When** it queries state\n163\t**Then** it reads from `sprint-state.json` directly (not sprint-status.yaml)\n164\t\n165\t### Story 11-3: State reconciliation on session start\n166\t\n167\tAs a developer,\n168\tI want state consistency verified at the start of every session,\n169\tSo that desyncs from crashes or manual edits are caught immediately.\n170\t\n171\t**Acceptance Criteria:**\n172\t\n173\t**Given** `sprint-state.json` and `sprint-status.yaml` are out of sync\n174\t**When** harness-run Step 1 pre-flight runs `reconcileState()`\n175\t**Then** `sprint-state.json` is authoritative and `sprint-status.yaml` is regenerated\n176\t\n177\t---\n178\t\n179\t## Epic 12: lib/ Restructuring\n180\t\n181\tSplit oversized files into domain subdirectories. Move business logic from commands to modules.\n182\t\n183\t### Story 12-1: Split coverage.ts into domain subdirectory\n184\t\n185\tAs a developer,\n186\tI want coverage logic in `src/lib/coverage/` with files under 300 lines each,\n187\tSo that coverage code is maintainable and testable.\n188\t\n189\t**Acceptance Criteria:**\n190\t\n191\t**Given** `src/lib/coverage/` exists\n192\t**When** inspected\n193\t**Then** it contains: `index.ts` (<50 lines, re-exports), `types.ts`, `runner.ts`, `evaluator.ts`, `parser.ts`\n194\t\n195\t**Given** each file in `src/lib/coverage/`\n196\t**When** line count is checked\n197\t**Then** no file exceeds 300 lines\n198\t\n199\t**Given** `parseTestCounts()` in `parser.ts`\n200\t**When** cargo workspace output is mixed with pytest-like output\n201\t**Then** cargo aggregation fires first (ordering guard test exists)\n202\t\n203\t### Story 12-2: Split docker.ts, otlp.ts, beads-sync.ts, doc-health.ts\n204\t\n205\tAs a developer,\n206\tI want all 832/590/422/378-line files split into domain subdirectories,\n207\tSo that the entire codebase respects the 300-line limit.\n208\t\n209\t**Acceptance Criteria:**\n210\t\n211\t**Given** `src/lib/docker/` with `compose.ts`, `health.ts`, `cleanup.ts`\n212\t**And** `src/lib/observability/` with `instrument.ts`, `config.ts`, `backends.ts`\n213\t**And** `src/lib/sync/` with `beads.ts`, `sprint-yaml.ts`, `story-files.ts`\n214\t**When** each file is checked\n215\t**Then** no file exceeds 300 lines\n216\t\n217\t**Given** all splits complete\n218\t**When** `npm test` runs\n219\t**Then** all tests pass with 0 regressions\n220\t\n221\t### Story 12-3: Move business logic from status.ts command to status module\n222\t\n223\tAs a developer,\n224\tI want `src/commands/status.ts` under 100 lines with logic in `src/modules/status/`,\n225\tSo that status logic is testable without command wiring.\n226\t\n227\t**Acceptance Criteria:**\n228\t\n229\t**Given** `src/modules/status/` with `index.ts`, `formatters.ts`, `endpoints.ts`, `drill-down.ts`\n230\t**When** `src/commands/status.ts` is inspected\n231\t**Then** it's under 100 lines — just arg parsing, module call, output formatting\n232\t\n233\t**Given** `src/modules/status/endpoints.ts`\n234\t**When** `buildScopedEndpoints()` is called\n235\t**Then** it produces the same URLs as the current `status.ts` implementation\n236\t\n237\t### Story 12-4: Shared test utilities and fixtures\n238\t\n239\tAs a developer,\n240\tI want reusable test helpers and fixtures,\n241\tSo that tests don't duplicate mock setup across 50+ files.\n242\t\n243\t**Acceptance Criteria:**\n244\t\n245\t**Given** `src/lib/__tests__/fixtures/` exists\n246\t**When** inspected\n247\t**Then** it contains: `cargo-toml-variants.ts`, `state-builders.ts`, `mock-factories.ts`\n248\t\n249\t**Given** `src/lib/__tests__/helpers.ts` exists\n250\t**When** test files import from it\n251\t**Then** common patterns (mock Docker, mock fs, create temp state) are one-liners\n252\t\n253\t---\n254\t\n255\t## Epic 13: Agent Abstraction\n256\t\n257\tRalph behind an AgentDriver interface.\n258\t\n259\t### Story 13-1: Create AgentDriver interface and types\n260\t\n261\tAs a developer,\n262\tI want an `AgentDriver` interface that abstracts agent execution,\n263\tSo that Ralph can be replaced or supplemented without touching 28 files.\n264\t\n265\t**Acceptance Criteria:**\n266\t\n267\t**Given** `src/lib/agents/types.ts` exists\n268\t**When** inspected\n269\t**Then** it defines `AgentDriver`, `AgentProcess`, `AgentEvent` types\n270\t\n271\t**Given** the `AgentEvent` type\n272\t**When** inspected\n273\t**Then** it covers: `tool-start`, `tool-complete`, `text`, `story-complete`, `story-failed`, `iteration`, `retry`, `result`\n274\t\n275\t### Story 13-2: Implement RalphDriver\n276\t\n277\tAs a developer,\n278\tI want Ralph wrapped in an `AgentDriver` implementation,\n279\tSo that ralph-specific behavior is isolated in one file.\n280\t\n281\t**Acceptance Criteria:**\n282\t\n283\t**Given** `src/lib/agents/ralph.ts` exists\n284\t**When** inspected\n285\t**Then** it implements `AgentDriver` with: `spawn()` (builds ralph.sh args), `parseOutput()` (parses ralph stderr + stream-json)\n286\t\n287\t**Given** `run-helpers.ts` ralph-specific functions (`parseRalphMessage`, `parseIterationMessage`, `buildSpawnArgs`)\n288\t**When** migration completes\n289\t**Then** they're moved into `ralph.ts` and `run-helpers.ts` is deleted\n290\t\n291\t### Story 13-3: Migrate run.ts to use AgentDriver\n292\t\n293\tAs a developer,\n294\tI want `run.ts` to use `AgentDriver` instead of directly spawning Ralph,\n295\tSo that the run command is agent-agnostic.\n296\t\n297\t**Acceptance Criteria:**\n298\t\n299\t**Given** `src/commands/run.ts`\n300\t**When** inspected\n301\t**Then** it imports `AgentDriver` and calls `driver.spawn()`, not `spawn('bash', [ralphPath, ...])`\n302\t\n303\t**Given** `resolveRalphPath()` in run.ts\n304\t**When** migration completes\n305\t**Then** it's moved into `ralph.ts` and run.ts uses `driver.getExecutablePath()`\n306\t\n307\t---\n308\t\n309\t## Epic 14: Process & Infrastructure Fixes\n310\t\n311\tRetro pipeline, tech debt gate, Docker fixes, observability choice, verify provisioning.\n312\t\n313\t### Story 14-1: Retro-to-sprint pipeline (Step 8b) + persistent epic-TD\n314\t\n315\tAs a developer running harness-run,\n316\tI want retro action items to auto-create stories under epic-TD,\n317\tSo that tech debt gets tracked and prioritized automatically.\n318\t\n319\t**Acceptance Criteria:**\n320\t\n321\t**Given** a retro file with `### Fix Now` items\n322\t**When** Step 8b runs\n323\t**Then** new `TD-N-slug: backlog` entries appear in sprint-state.json under epic-TD\n324\t\n325\t**Given** `epic-TD` doesn't exist\n326\t**When** Step 8b creates the first TD story\n327\t**Then** `epic-TD` is created with `status: in-progress` (never transitions to `done`)\n328\t\n329\t**Given** a duplicate action item (80%+ word overlap with existing TD story)\n330\t**When** Step 8b processes it\n331\t**Then** it's skipped with `[INFO]` message\n332\t\n333\t### Story 14-2: Tech debt gate in story selection\n334\t\n335\tAs a developer,\n336\tI want TD stories prioritized before new feature work,\n337\tSo that debt gets paid before it accumulates further.\n338\t\n339\t**Acceptance Criteria:**\n340\t\n341\t**Given** `epic-TD` has 3 backlog stories and a feature epic has 5 backlog stories\n342\t**When** harness-run Step 2 selects next story\n343\t**Then** TD stories are selected first\n344\t\n345\t**Given** all TD stories are `done`\n346\t**When** Step 2 selects next story\n347\t**Then** feature epic stories are selected normally\n348\t\n349\t### Story 14-3: Docker pre-check and orphan cleanup\n350\t\n351\tAs a developer,\n352\tI want Docker availability checked BEFORE any verification attempt,\n353\tSo that sessions don't burn 30 minutes on Docker failures.\n354\t\n355\t**Acceptance Criteria:**\n356\t\n357\t**Given** Docker daemon is not running\n358\t**When** harness-run Step 1 pre-flight runs\n359\t**Then** it fails fast with `[FAIL] Docker not available` without attempting any verification\n360\t\n361\t**Given** a leftover `codeharness-verify` container from a crashed session\n362\t**When** Step 1 pre-flight runs\n363\t**Then** the orphaned container is removed\n364\t\n365\t### Story 14-4: Observability backend choice (Victoria vs ELK vs Remote)\n366\t\n367\tAs a developer initializing codeharness,\n368\tI want to choose my observability backend and provide remote endpoints,\n369\tSo that I'm not locked into VictoriaMetrics with hardcoded ports.\n370\t\n371\t**Acceptance Criteria:**\n372\t\n373\t**Given** `codeharness init --observability-backend elk`\n374\t**When** init runs\n375\t**Then** state stores `otlp.backend: 'elk'` and ELK compose is used\n376\t\n377\t**Given** `codeharness init --otel-endpoint https://remote:4318 --logs-url https://remote:9200`\n378\t**When** init runs\n379\t**Then** no local Docker stack is started and state stores remote endpoints\n380\t\n381\t**Given** `otlp.backend` is `'elk'`\n382\t**When** `codeharness status --check-docker` runs\n383\t**Then** it checks ELK containers (not Victoria)\n384\t\n385\t### Story 14-5: Stack-aware verification Dockerfile generation\n386\t\n387\tAs a developer verifying a Rust/Bevy project,\n388\tI want the verification Dockerfile generated with the correct toolchain and system libs,\n389\tSo that verification doesn't waste time fixing container issues manually.\n390\t\n391\t**Acceptance Criteria:**\n392\t\n393\t**Given** a Rust project with `bevy` in Cargo.toml\n394\t**When** `verify-env build` runs\n395\t**Then** the generated Dockerfile includes: correct Rust version, Bevy system libs (wayland, udev, alsa, x11, xkbcommon, fontconfig), clippy, cargo-tarpaulin\n396\t\n397\t**Given** `ENV PATH=\"/root/.cargo/bin:$PATH\"` in the generated Dockerfile\n398\t**When** `cargo tarpaulin` is run inside the container\n399\t**Then** it works without manual `source \"$HOME/.cargo/env\"`\n400\t\n401\t### Story 14-6: Subagent status ownership + time budget awareness\n402\t\n403\tAs a developer running harness-run,\n404\tI want the orchestrator to own all status writes and respect time budgets,\n405\tSo that status is always correct and sessions don't fail at verification.\n406\t\n407\t**Acceptance Criteria:**\n408\t\n409\t**Given** a subagent completes dev-story but doesn't update sprint-state.json\n410\t**When** the orchestrator checks after subagent return\n411\t**Then** it updates the status itself\n412\t\n413\t**Given** 10 minutes remaining and next phase is verification (~20min)\n414\t**When** harness-run checks budget\n415\t**Then** it defers with `[INFO] deferring verify to next session`\n416\t\n417\t### Story 14-7: Fix beads sync, session flags, ralph story tracking, proof docs\n418\t\n419\tAs a developer,\n420\tI want chronic infrastructure bugs fixed,\n421\tSo that sessions stop wasting time on known issues.\n422\t\n423\t**Acceptance Criteria:**\n424\t\n425\t**Given** a story file with `## Status: backlog` header\n426\t**When** `readStoryFileStatus()` runs\n427\t**Then** it returns `'backlog'` (handles `##` prefix)\n428\t\n429\t**Given** `bd` CLI is not installed\n430\t**When** `codeharness sync` runs\n431\t**Then** it prints `[INFO] beads CLI not installed — skipping` (not `[FAIL]`)\n432\t\n433\t**Given** `cargo test` passes\n434\t**When** `codeharness.local.md` is checked\n435\t**Then** `session_flags.tests_passed` is `true`\n436\t\n437\t**Given** ralph times out during a story\n438\t**When** timeout report is generated\n439\t**Then** `status.json` contains the correct `story` field (not `unknown`)\n440\t\n441\t**Given** the codeharness proof format\n442\t**When** `commands/harness-verify.md` is read\n443\t**Then** the expected markdown structure is documented\n444\t\n445\t---\n446\t\n447\t## Epic 15: Enforcement\n448\t\n449\tCI gates, ESLint rules, boundary tests, template migration.\n450\t\n451\t### Story 15-1: CI file size gate + fix remaining violations\n452\t\n453\tAs a developer,\n454\tI want a CI check that fails if any `.ts` file exceeds 300 lines,\n455\tSo that file size debt stops accumulating.\n456\t\n457\t**Acceptance Criteria:**\n458\t\n459\t**Given** CI pipeline runs\n460\t**When** any `.ts` file in `src/` (excluding `__tests__/`) exceeds 300 lines\n461\t**Then** the build fails with the filename and line count\n462\t\n463\t**Given** all file splits from Epic 12 are complete\n464\t**When** CI gate is enabled\n465\t**Then** it passes (zero violations)\n466\t\n467\t### Story 15-2: ESLint no-empty-catch + boundary tests\n468\t\n469\tAs a developer,\n470\tI want automated enforcement of error handling and module boundaries,\n471\tSo that architectural rules aren't just documented but enforced.\n472\t\n473\t**Acceptance Criteria:**\n474\t\n475\t**Given** ESLint runs\n476\t**When** a catch block is empty (no `// IGNORE:` comment)\n477\t**Then** it reports an error\n478\t\n479\t**Given** a boundary test scans `src/`\n480\t**When** it finds `stack === 'nodejs'` outside `src/lib/stacks/`\n481\t**Then** the test fails\n482\t\n483\t**Given** a boundary test scans module imports\n484\t**When** a module imports from another module's internal file (not index.ts)\n485\t**Then** the test fails\n486\t\n487\t### Story 15-3: Template migration — all templates to static files\n488\t\n489\tAs a developer,\n490\tI want all templates in `templates/` as static files (not generated in TypeScript),\n491\tSo that there's one template system.\n492\t\n493\t**Acceptance Criteria:**\n494\t\n495\t**Given** `templates/dockerfiles/`, `templates/prompts/`, `templates/docs/` directories\n496\t**When** inspected\n497\t**Then** they contain all Dockerfile templates, prompt templates, and doc templates that were previously in `src/templates/*.ts`\n498\t\n499\t**Given** `src/templates/` TypeScript generators\n500\t**When** migration completes\n501\t**Then** they're replaced with `renderTemplate()` calls reading from `templates/`\n502\t\n503\t**Given** `renderTemplate('templates/dockerfiles/Dockerfile.nodejs', { TARBALL: 'package.tgz' })`\n504\t**When** called\n505\t**Then** it returns the same Dockerfile content as the current `nodejsTemplate()` function\n506\t\n507\t### Story 15-4: Fix ~40 TS compilation errors in test files\n508\t\n509\tAs a developer,\n510\tI want `npx tsc --noEmit` to produce zero errors,\n511\tSo that type safety is enforced across the entire codebase.\n512\t\n513\t**Acceptance Criteria:**\n514\t\n515\t**Given** `npx tsc --noEmit` is run\n516\t**When** it completes\n517\t**Then** zero compilation errors (down from ~40)\n518\t\n519\t**Given** the fixes\n520\t**When** inspected\n521\t**Then** they're type annotation changes only — no logic changes\n522\t\n523\t### Story 15-5: Lint rule for bare exception swallowing\n524\t\n525\tAs a developer,\n526\tI want code review to flag `except Exception: pass` (Python) and empty catch blocks,\n527\tSo that error swallowing doesn't cause silent production incidents.\n528\t\n529\t**Acceptance Criteria:**\n530\t\n531\t**Given** code-review subagent reviews Python code\n532\t**When** it finds `except Exception: pass`\n533\t**Then** it flags it as HIGH severity\n534\t\n535\t**Given** `post-write-check.sh` hook runs after writing a Python file\n536\t**When** the file contains `except Exception: pass`\n537\t**Then** it prints a warning\n538\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01L1PJWbRWqo4hkWCH9DV9Tr","session_id":"a1f3179e-0b63-4a22-aa4b-b755c26a5a4c","uuid":"3b0cb16f-9375-43fb-80c8-a24dc1df3e3d","timestamp":"2026-04-02T20:26:16.406Z"}
